------------------------------------------------\n\n::: dom/xul/XULDocument.cpp\n@@ +2649,5 @@\n>                             NodePrincipal(),\n> +                           documentIsChrome\n> +                             ? nsILoadInfo::SEC_REQUIRE_SAME_ORIGIN_DATA_INHERITS |\n> +                               nsILoadInfo::SEC_ALLOW_CHROME\n> +                             : nsILoadInfo::SEC_REQUIRE_SAME_ORIGIN_DATA_INHERITS,\n\nYou probably still need to use SEC_FORCE_INHERIT_PRINCIPAL for the reasons mentioned in the comment.\n\nAnd chrome documents use the system principal, which is always allowed to load from anywhere. So just use\n\nSEC_REQUIRE_SAME_ORIGIN_DATA_INHERITS | SEC_FORCE_INHERIT_PRINCIPAL\n\n(also no need to mention this in the comment as what you say there is always true for same-origin loads)", "author": "jonas@sicking.cc", "id": 10786885, "time": "2015-09-29T03:09:12Z"}, {"text": "Created attachment 8667077\nbug_1206958_xuldocument.patch\n\n(In reply to Jonas Sicking (:sicking) from comment #2)\n> And chrome documents use the system principal, which is always allowed to\n> load from anywhere. So just use\n> \n> SEC_REQUIRE_SAME_ORIGIN_DATA_INHERITS | SEC_FORCE_INHERIT_PRINCIPAL\n\nThat is quite nifty - thanks!", "author": "ckerschb@christophkerschbaumer.com", "id": 10786899, "time": "2015-09-29T03:17:19Z"}, {"text": "https://hg.mozilla.org/integration/mozilla-inbound/rev/8b11ccff38b2", "author": "pulsebot@bots.tld", "id": 10792382, "time": "2015-09-30T03:07:07Z"}, {"text": "https://hg.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/rev/8b11ccff38b2", "author": "cbook@mozilla.com", "id": 10793757, "time": "2015-09-30T11:53:32Z"}], "cf_last_resolved": "2015-09-30T11:53:32Z", "priority": "--", "mentors_detail": [], "cf_crash_signature": "", "version": "unspecified", "cf_qa_whiteboard": "", "cf_tracking_firefox_esr52": "---", "cf_tracking_firefox59": "---", "last_change_time": "2015-09-30T11:53:32Z", "cf_platform_rel": "---", "product": "Core", "cf_status_firefox_esr52"